// ============================================================================
// v17.21 CHANGELOG — FINAL EQ LINE FIX + HUD TEXT UNIFORMITY
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-16] v17.21 — Visual-Only Update (NO logic/filter/alert changes)
//
// FIX 1: HUD TEXT UNIFORMITY
//   - ALL value cells now use the same bright silver color (color.silver, 0%)
//   - Matches the "MSS-Retrace" Entry Mode color for uniform readability
//   - REMOVED all conditional dimming (gray30) for inactive rows
//   - Color exceptions preserved:
//     * INVALIDATED/killed → color.red (0%)
//     * TRAP BUY/TRAP SELL → color.orange (0%)
//     * ALIGNED → color.lime (0%)
//     * Signal fired (FIRE stage, alerts, signals today) → color.lime (0%)
//     * Everything else → color.silver (0%) — bright, uniform
//
// FIX 2: EQ LINE — FINAL ROOT CAUSE FIX (delete-and-redraw EVERY bar)
//   - REMOVED barstate.islast guard — line now redraws on EVERY bar
//   - Uses user-specified exact pattern: delete → line.new(bar_index-1..bar_index)
//   - extend=extend.right ensures full chart coverage from a 1-bar segment
//   - EQ label also uses delete-and-redraw every bar
//   - eq_level calculated as exact (h4RangeHigh + h4RangeLow) / 2.0
//   - Width=5, color=white, style=solid — maximum visibility
//
// ============================================================================
// v17.20 CHANGELOG — CRITICAL EQ LINE Z-ORDER FIX + NAVY BLUE HUD
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-16] v17.20 — Visual-Only Update (NO logic/filter/alert changes)
//
// FIX 1 (CRITICAL): EQ Line Z-Order — NOW VISIBLE ABOVE P&D ZONE BOXES
//   - ROOT CAUSE: EQ line was drawn inside the same block as zone boxes,
//     causing the filled box area to paint over the line on the chart.
//   - SOLUTION: Separated EQ line + label into its own dedicated block that
//     executes AFTER all box drawing, using delete-and-redraw every bar.
//   - Pattern: line.delete(pdEqLine) → line.new() ensures line is ALWAYS
//     the last visual element rendered (topmost z-order layer).
//   - Width increased: 4 → 5 for maximum visibility
//   - Color: color.white (pure white, 0% transparency)
//   - Style: line.style_solid, extend.right
//   - EQ Label: solid black background (0% transparency), size.normal
//
// FIX 2: HUD Navy Blue Background
//   - REMOVED: color.new(color.black, 40) — old black glass
//   - REPLACED: color.new(#1a237e, 20) — Deep Navy Blue, 80% visible
//   - Header row: color.new(#0d47a1, 10) — Brighter navy for prominence
//   - Table frame border: color.new(color.white, 60) — visible white border
//
// FIX 3: HUD Color Hierarchy Update
//   - All labels: color.white
//   - Active values: color.new(color.lime, 0)
//   - Inactive values: color.new(color.silver, 0)
//   - Warnings: color.new(color.orange, 0)
//   - Invalidated: color.new(color.red, 0)
//
// Plot budget: 33/64 (unchanged — no new plots)
// ZERO logic/filter/alert architecture changes
// ============================================================================

