// ============================================================================
// v17.14.1 CHANGELOG — KILL ZONE PAYLOAD INTEGRATION
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-13] v17.14.1 — Add Kill Zone to webhook alert payloads
//   - Added "kill_zone": {{plot_12}} to all 4 alertcondition() JSON payloads
//   - kzCode was already exposed as plot_12 since v17.12.3; now included in alerts
//   - Kill Zone mapping: 0=Off-Session, 1=London, 2=NY AM, 3=NY PM, 4=Asian
//   - Enables session-based analytics in TradeX tracker
//   - Updated version strings from "v17.14" to "v17.14.1"
//   - No logic, plot budget, or visual changes
//
// [2026-05-13] v17.14 — Fix chart spam, harden dedup, restore production thresholds
//
// BUG 1 — CHART LABEL SPAM (P0):
//   Debug labels (label.new) fired on EVERY historical bar that met conditions.
//   With thresholds at 0, this created hundreds of overlapping labels.
//   FIX: Debug labels now gated by barstate.islastconfirmedhistory (last bar only).
//   Additionally, labels use var+delete pattern — max 1 label per alert type.
//
// BUG 2 — WEAK DEDUP ON HISTORY:
//   setup_id changes every bar (confluence/stage shift), so dedup was ineffective.
//   FIX: Dedup now uses DIRECTION+ZONE only (e.g. "BULL_DZ") — stable across bars.
//   Cooldown is purely bar-count based, no longer bypassed by setup_id change.
//
// BUG 3 — RE10045 EMPTY ARRAY (from v17.13):
//   for loop on empty debug arrays crashed. FIX: if dbg_rows > 0 guard.
//
// BUG 4 — CE10123 SERIES STRING IN ALERTCONDITION (from v17.13):
//   FIX: Static "dynamic" placeholder in message (Pine requires const string).
//
// RESTORED: Production thresholds (confluence=4, stage=5, retrace=2, cooldown=60).
//   Debug mode defaults to OFF. Enable manually for testing.
//
// Plot budget: 32/64 (unchanged from v17.13)
// ============================================================================

// ============================================================================
// v17.13 CHANGELOG — ALERT CONSOLIDATION & HARDENING SYSTEM
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-13] v17.13 — Production Alert System Overhaul (P0 SAFETY-CRITICAL)
//
// CONSOLIDATION: Reduced from 15 alertcondition() to exactly 4:
//   1. Sniper Long    2. Sniper Short    3. Retrace Long    4. Retrace Short
//
// FIRING RULES:
//   Sniper: Action Step==READY, Confluence>=threshold, dtStage>=threshold,
//           Guardian not TRAP, State Machine not BLOCKED, deduplicated
//   Retrace: Correct P&D zone, Guardian allows retrace, Confluence>=threshold
//
// DEDUPLICATION: setup_id (e.g. "BULL_DZ_CF4_S5") prevents duplicate fires
// COOLDOWN: Configurable minutes between same-type alerts (default 60)
// DEBUG MODE: Optional labels + table showing last N alerts on chart
// HUD: New "Last Alert" row after Action Plan
// WEBHOOK PAYLOADS: Exact JSON spec with correct {{plot_X}} references
//
// Plot budget: 32/64 (reduced from 47 — removed 15 alertconditions, added 4)
// ============================================================================

// ============================================================================
// v17.12.3 CHANGELOG — ALERTCONDITION PAYLOAD FIX
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-12] v17.12.3 — Corrected All alertcondition() {{plot_X}} References
//
// ROOT CAUSE: When v17.12 consolidated plots from 38→18, the {{plot_X}}
// references inside alertcondition JSON payloads were not fully updated to
// match the new plot order. This caused webhook payloads to send scrambled
// data (e.g., stop_loss referencing quality_score's plot).
//
// FIX: Updated all 12 alertcondition() payloads to use correct plot mapping:
//   plot_0: entryLong      plot_6:  qualityScore    plot_12: kzCode
//   plot_1: slLong         plot_7:  poiScore        plot_13: guardianCode
//   plot_2: tpLong         plot_8:  confluenceScore  plot_14: displacement
//   plot_3: entryShort     plot_9:  dtStage          plot_15: momentumScore
//   plot_4: slShort        plot_10: h4Bias           plot_16: h4FibLevel
//   plot_5: tpShort        plot_11: pdZone           plot_17: structureStateCode
//
// RESULT: All webhook JSON payloads now contain correct field→plot mappings.
//         Plot count unchanged at 28/64.
//
// ============================================================================
// v17.12.2 CHANGELOG — EQUILIBRIUM LABEL FIX
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-12] v17.12.2 — Remove "H4 Equilibrium" Label from Chart
//
// FIX: The plot-based equilibrium line (yellow circles) was still showing
// "SMC PD v17:H4 Equilibrium" label on the chart price axis due to
// trackprice=true. In Pine Script, even with title="", trackprice shows
// the indicator name prefix as a label.
//
// CHANGE: Replaced trackprice=true with display=display.pane
//   - display.pane: Renders the plot on the chart pane ONLY (no data window, no legend)
//   - trackprice removed: Eliminates the price-axis label entirely
//   - The line.new-based equilibrium line (yellow dotted) remains the primary visual
//   - The plot circles provide additional visual reinforcement on the pane
//
// RESULT: No more "H4 Equilibrium" text floating on the chart.
//         Plot count unchanged (still within safe limits).
//
// ============================================================================
// v17.12 CHANGELOG — CRITICAL PLOT BUDGET FIX (65 → 28 PLOTS)
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-12] v17.12 — Consolidated Alert Data Plots to Fix RE10140 Error
//
// ROOT CAUSE: v17.11.1 exceeded TradingView's 64-plot limit (reported as 65 plots).
// The issue was from 38 hidden "Alert" plots (display=display.none) used only 
// for webhook {{plot_X}} references in alertconditions.
//
// FIX: Consolidated alert plots from 38 down to 18 (20-plot reduction).
// REMOVED (non-critical data):
//   - FVG Filter, OB Refinement: Inferred from poiScore
//   - Asian High/Low/Pips: Not needed for real-time signals
//   - AMD Phase, IPM flags, CT Lite flags: Secondary alerts (not critical path)
//   - Tier3 Confluence/PoolMask: Redundant with poiScore
//   - Entry/TP Mode Flags: Static configuration data
//   - Momentum Flags: Derived from momentumScore
//   - MSS POI Top/Bot: Internal intermediate state
//   - Re-Entry prices: Visualized separately (not needed in webhook)
//
// KEPT (essential data):
//   - Entry/SL/TP prices: Critical for trade execution
//   - Quality metrics: Confluence, POI, DT Stage
//   - H4 Structure: Bias, P&D Zone, Kill Zone, Guardian Code
//   - Technical indicators: Displacement, Momentum, Fib Level, Structure State
//
// RESULT: Plot count reduced to 28/64 (safe margin of 36 plots).
// All core trading signal functionality fully preserved.
// Webhook payloads updated to reference new plot numbers.
//
// ============================================================================
// v17.11.1 CHANGELOG — EQUILIBRIUM LINE & ZONE PROPORTION VERIFICATION
// ============================================================================
// [2026-05-12] v17.11.1 — Equilibrium Line Enhancement & Zone Diagnostics
//
// FIX 1 — VISIBLE EQUILIBRIUM LINE:
//   The equilibrium line (50% midpoint) has been significantly enhanced:
//   - Increased width from 1 to 2 for better visibility
//   - Changed color from gray(40% transparent) to solid yellow(20% transparent)
//   - Added a plot-based backup line (circles style) for trackprice support
//   - New toggle "Show Equilibrium Line" in Visual Settings
//
// FIX 2 — ZONE PROPORTION DIAGNOSTICS:
//   New HUD row "Zone Ratio" shows real-time PZ/EQ/DZ percentage split.
//   Displays: "PZ:33.0% EQ:34.0% DZ:33.0% (Target: 33/34/33)"
//   Helps verify zones are correctly proportioned at a glance.
//
// FIX 3 — PREMIUM/DISCOUNT THRESHOLD LINES:
//   Added two subtle dashed lines at the Premium Bottom (66.7%) and 
//   Discount Top (33.3%) boundaries for clearer zone demarcation.
//
// Plot budget: 63/64 (+1 plot for equilibrium line)
// ============================================================================
// v17.11 CHANGELOG — FLEXIBLE P&D ZONE RANGE CONTROLS
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// [2026-05-12] v17.11 — Flexible Zone Range Configuration for Intraday Trading
//
// PROBLEM: Previous versions used a fixed 50-bar H4 lookback, creating zones
//   that were too large for intraday trading (often 300-400+ pips). Discount
//   zones frequently fell off-screen, making them useless for day trading.
//
// FIX 1 — ZONE SOURCE TOGGLE:
//   New input "Zone Source" with 3 options:
//   - SESSION: Today's high/low only (scalping)
//   - RECENT: Last N H4 bars — user-configurable (day trading, DEFAULT)
//   - MACRO: Full historical swing (50 bars, swing trading)
//
// FIX 2 — ZONE LOOKBACK CONTROL:
//   "Zone Lookback (H4 Bars)" input: 5-100, default 20
//   20 bars × 4H = ~3.3 trading days — ideal for day trading
//   Replaces the hardcoded 50-bar lookback when in RECENT mode
//
// FIX 3 — MAX ZONE HEIGHT CAP:
//   "Max Zone Height (× ATR)" input: 5.0-50.0, default 15.0
//   If the calculated zone exceeds this cap, it compresses to a smaller
//   recent lookback (10 H4 bars) to keep zones actionable.
//   Can be disabled via "Enable Zone Height Cap" toggle.
//
// FIX 4 — MINIMUM ZONE HEIGHT FLOOR:
//   Zones cannot collapse below 2 × H4 ATR, ensuring meaningful PZ/DZ/EQ.
//
// FIX 5 — ZONE CONFIG HUD DIAGNOSTICS:
//   Enhanced Zone Debug rows show: Source, Lookback, Zone Height, Max Height,
//   and whether the height cap was applied (✓ OK or ⚠ CAPPED).
//
// PRESETS:
//   Scalping:     SESSION, LB=10, MaxH=10×ATR
//   Day Trading:  RECENT,  LB=20, MaxH=15×ATR (DEFAULT)
//   Swing:        MACRO,   LB=50, MaxH=25×ATR (or disabled)
//
// Plot budget: 62/64 (unchanged — no new plots or alertconditions)
// request.security calls: 10/40 (added 2 for H4 ATR and compressed range)
// ============================================================================
// v17.10 CHANGELOG — GUARDIAN & ACTION STEP NEUTRAL BIAS LOGIC
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// [2026-05-12] v17.10 — Minor refinements for Guardian & Action Step consistency
//
// FIX 1 — GUARDIAN NEUTRAL GATE:
//   When H4 Bias = NEUTRAL (h4Bias == 0), Guardian can no longer suggest
//   directional bias. Instead of showing RETRACE BUY/SELL or TRAP BUY/SELL,
//   Guardian now displays "⏸ WAITING" in gray.
//   - Guardian only shows directional status when H4 Bias is confirmed
//     (BULLISH or BEARISH)
//   - Eliminates contradictory signals: NEUTRAL bias + directional Guardian
//
// FIX 2 — ACTION STEP NEUTRAL GATE:
//   When H4 Bias = NEUTRAL, Action Step can no longer show HUNTING,
//   MONITORING, or READY — these all require directional context.
//   New behavior:
//   - STANDBY (gray) when NEUTRAL and no active trade/invalidation
//   - Action Plan: "Neutral bias — wait for H4 directional confirmation"
//   - INVALIDATED and ACTIVE states unaffected (always shown if applicable)
//
// FIX 3 — CROSS-TIMEFRAME ACTION STEP CONSISTENCY:
//   Since H4 Bias, zone detection, and invalidation all already use
//   request.security("240",...) from v17.7, Action Step is inherently
//   timeframe-consistent. This version adds explicit h4Bias==0 gates
//   to HUNTING, MONITORING, and READY states to ensure they cannot
//   activate without confirmed directional bias on ANY timeframe.
//
// VALIDATION:
//   - H4 Bias NEUTRAL → Guardian shows "⏸ WAITING" (not RETRACE/TRAP)
//   - H4 Bias NEUTRAL → Action Step shows "STANDBY" (not HUNTING)
//   - H4 Bias BULLISH/BEARISH → Normal Guardian and Action Step behavior
//   - 5M, 15M, 1H, 4H all show identical Action Step for same conditions
//
// Plot budget: 62/64 (unchanged — logic changes only, no new plots)
// ============================================================================
// v17.9 CHANGELOG — ZONE DETECTION FIX + DIAGNOSTIC VISIBILITY
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// CRITICAL FIX: PZ/DZ/EQ zone detection was using a 10% neutral zone width,
//   creating an extremely narrow EQ band (only ±5% of range around midpoint).
//   This caused prices clearly in the middle third to show as PZ or DZ.
//
// ROOT CAUSE: neutralZoneWidth defaulted to 10.0 (= ±5% of range for EQ).
//   With a 5-point range (e.g. 211-216), EQ was only 213.25-213.75 (0.5 pts).
//   Price at 213.277 SHOULD be in EQ with classic thirds but was shown as DZ/PZ
//   whenever the 4H range recalculated and shifted boundaries slightly.
//
// FIX 1: Changed neutralZoneWidth default from 10.0 to 33.3 (classic thirds).
//   - Premium Zone (PZ): top 1/3 of range (above 66.7% mark)
//   - Discount Zone (DZ): bottom 1/3 of range (below 33.3% mark)
//   - Equilibrium (EQ): middle 1/3 of range (33.3% to 66.7%)
//   - Max value raised from 25.0 to 50.0 for flexibility
//
// FIX 2: Added Zone Debug diagnostic row to HUD showing:
//   - RH (Range High), RL (Range Low), PT (Premium Threshold), DT (Discount Threshold)
//   - Current close and boolean zone states (P/E/D)
//   This allows real-time validation of zone calculations on any pair.
//
// FIX 3: Added 3 debug alertconditions for zone transitions (Premium/EQ/DZ entry).
//
// INCLUDES all v17.7 fixes (H4 range via request.security) and v17.8 fixes
// (zone position independent of bias direction).
//
// VALIDATION: Price at 213.277 with range 211-216 must show "EQ (gray)".
//   Premium threshold = 214.35, Discount threshold = 212.65.
// ============================================================================
// v17.6 CHANGELOG — TACTICAL GUIDANCE & VISUAL LAYERING
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// [2026-05-12] v17.6 — Action Step, Action Plan & P&D Layering Fix
//
// FEATURE 1 — ACTION STEP (replaces "Readiness" row):
//   6-state lifecycle guidance for the trader:
//     STANDBY  (Gray)   — Outside Kill Zone OR Bias/Alignment conflict
//     HUNTING  (Blue)   — In KZ, Aligned, but price in Equilibrium (no P&D zone)
//     MONITORING (Amber) — Price in correct P&D zone but Sniper Stage < 4
//     READY    (Green)  — Confluence ≥ 4 AND Sniper Stage = 5/5
//     ACTIVE   (Purple) — State Machine active (trade being managed)
//     INVALIDATED (Red) — Setup killed by hard invalidation
//
// FEATURE 2 — ACTION PLAN (new HUD row):
//   Contextual forward-looking instruction based on current state:
//   - "Standby for next Kill Zone session"
//   - "Wait for Dip to Discount for Long"
//   - "Wait for Retrace to Premium for Short"
//   - "Watch for Sniper Trigger"
//   - "Manage trade per Entry Mode rules"
//   - "Stand down — setup killed"
//
// FEATURE 3 — P&D ZONE VISUAL LAYERING FIX:
//   - P&D zones now use wide right offset (+500 bars) for full visibility
//   - Increased transparency to 92% (from 88%) for cleaner candle visibility
//   - P&D box creation remains BEFORE S&D zones for proper draw order
//   - Equilibrium line uses extend=extend.right for infinite projection
//   - Candle bodies and wicks clearly visible on top of zone shading
//
// HUD: 18 rows (was 16). "Readiness" replaced by "Action Step" + "Action Plan"
// Plot budget: 59/64 (unchanged — new logic uses no plots)
//
// ============================================================================

// ============================================================================
// v17.5 CHANGELOG — UNIFIED STATE-AWARE DECISION ENGINE
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// [2026-05-12] v17.5 ARCHITECTURAL REWRITE — Synchronized HUD & Gating
//
// Carries forward all v17.0–v17.5 fixes.
//
// FIX 1 — REPLACE signalCounter WITH REAL-TIME CONFLUENCE SCORE:
//   - Removed cumulative signalCounter (misleading historical artifact)
//   - New confluenceScore computed fresh on EVERY bar from 6 real-time components:
//     (1) Sniper Progress (dtStage) >= 4   (+1)
//     (2) POI Score >= 3                    (+1)
//     (3) Displacement active (>= 0.5 ATR) (+1)
//     (4) Momentum clean (score < 2)        (+1)
//     (5) Kill Zone active                  (+1)
//     (6) Alignment valid (no conflict)     (+1)
//   - Hard gate: capped at 3 unless POI >= 3 AND Displacement >= 0.5× ATR
//   - Forced to 0 when both State Machine sides = IDLE
//   - HUD renamed "Signal" → "Confluence"
//
// FIX 2 — SNIPER PROGRESS (dtStage) RESET LOGIC:
//   - dtStage now resets to 0 on:
//     (a) H4 bias change (h4BiasChanged)
//     (b) Any invalidation event (longKilledThisBar / shortKilledThisBar)
//     (c) Session/day boundary (newDay)
//     (d) Inactivity decay: auto-reset if no progression in 30 bars
//   - Prevents permanent "Stage 5/5" display
//   - HUD renamed "Sniper State" → "Sniper Progress"
//
// FIX 3 — GUARDIAN ↔ CONFLUENCE SYNCHRONIZATION:
//   - If Guardian = TRAP (code 5/6), confluenceScore capped at max 2
//   - Guardian SNIPER mode display requires confluenceScore >= 5
//   - Eliminates contradiction: TRAP + high readiness impossible
//
// FIX 4 — KILL ZONE VISUAL SUPPRESSION:
//   - When Outside KZ: confluenceScore capped at max 3
//   - When Outside KZ: Sniper Progress display downgraded by 1 stage
//   - Internal detection logic remains 100% active (no execution logic change)
//
// FIX 5 — STATE MACHINE → HUD INTEGRATION:
//   - When L:IDLE AND S:IDLE: confluenceScore forced = 0
//   - When L:IDLE AND S:IDLE: Sniper Progress shows "IDLE" (not stage number)
//   - When IDLE: Guardian blocked from showing SNIPER mode
//   - New unified readiness layer: READY / BLOCKED / ACTIVE / INVALID
//
// FIX 6 — INVALIDATION LABEL DEDUPLICATION:
//   - Per-bar tracking: lastInvalBarLong / lastInvalBarShort
//   - Only ONE invalidation "X" label per bar per direction
//   - Prevents stacking 3-4 "X" labels on same candle
//
// FIX 7 — HUD NAMING CORRECTIONS:
//   - "Signal" → "Confluence" (real-time score, not counter)
//   - "Sniper State" → "Sniper Progress" (reflects staged readiness)
//   - New "Readiness" row: READY / BLOCKED / ACTIVE / INVALID
//
// Plot budget: 59/64 (unchanged from v17.5)
//
// [2026-05-12] v17.5 FINAL — All Hatching Removed, Solid P&D Zones
//   ROOT CAUSE OF HATCHING: box.new() called every bar/tick without deleting old boxes
//   → dozens of overlapping boxes created the hatched/striped visual artifact.
//
//   FIX A — P&D EXTENDING ZONES (now SOLID fills, zero hatching):
//     * Changed from naked box.new() to var box + delete-then-recreate pattern
//     * Only ONE premium box and ONE discount box exist at any time
//     * Solid red fill (88% transparent) for Premium, solid green for Discount
//
//   FIX B — REMOVED FVG MICRO-ZONE CANDLE OVERLAYS:
//     * These drew a new box on EVERY bar where FVG was active → overlapping = hatching
//     * FVG detection logic remains 100% active for POI scoring and signals
//
//   FIX C — REMOVED OB MICRO-ZONE CANDLE OVERLAYS:
//     * Same issue as FVG: new box per bar while price in OB → overlapping = hatching
//     * OB detection logic remains 100% active for POI scoring and signals
//
//   PRESERVED: Supply/Demand zones (solid fills, purple borders, large white labels)
//   Plot budget unchanged: 59/64 (box.new has zero plot cost)
// ============================================================================

